Package: epmr
Title: Tools for Educational and Psychological Measurement
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Anthony", "Albano", email = "tony.d.albano@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
URL: https://github.com/talbano/epmr, https://www.thetaminusb.com/intro-measurement-r/
Description: The epmr package contains tools for creating and evaluating tests
    in the social sciences, primarily in the contexts of education and
    psychology. The package accompanies the book Introduction to Educational
    and Psychological Measurement in R (free online, see link below). Example
    data come from the 2009 PISA study and the BDI-II. Functions currently
    support classical item and distractor analysis, reliability analysis,
    factor analysis, some item response theory, and analysis of differential
    item functioning.
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports: lme4, dplyr, tibble, ggplot2
Encoding: UTF-8
License: GPL-3 + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
Suggests: knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
